{"lemma":"أُمِّ","slug":"أُمِّ","root":"#.م.م","root_slug":"_-م-م","root_link":"/words/roots/_-م-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أُمّ","root":"أمم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":35},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1169","n1170","n1171"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8F%D9%85%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to respire thirstily"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to smoke"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to precede"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to govern, to lead"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1169","headword_ar":"اَمْ","root":"Am","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is a conjunction, (S, M, K,) connected with what precedes it (Msb, Mughnee) so that neither what precedes it nor what follows it is independent, the one of the other. (Mughnee.) It denotes interrogation; (M, K;) or is used in a case of interrogation, (S, Msb,) corresponding to the interrogative"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a","text_ar":"اَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aY~","text_ar":"اَىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or, as Z says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aY~u AlA^amorayoni kaAy^inN","text_ar":"اَىُّ الاَمْرَيْنِ كَايِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [for an explanation of which, see what follows;] (Mughnee;) or, [in other words,] corresponding to the interrogative"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a","text_ar":"اَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", whereby, and by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amo","text_ar":"اَمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", one seeks, or desires, particularization: (Mughnee:) it is as though it were an interrogative after an interrogative. (Lth, T.) Thus you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azayudN fiY Ald~aAri A^amo EamorNw","text_ar":"اَزَيُدٌ فِى الدَّارِ اَمْ عَمْرٌو"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Is Zeyd in the house, or 'Amr?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, Mughnee;) i. e. which of them two ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ay~uhumaA","text_ar":"اَيُّهُمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":") is in the house? (S;) therefore what follows"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Am","text_ar":"ام"},{"kind":"text","text":"and what precedes it compose one sentence; and it is not used in commanding nor in forbidding; and what follows it must correspond to what precedes it in the quality of noun and of verb; so that you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azayodN qaAy^imN A^amE qaAEidN","text_ar":"اَزَيْدٌ قَايِمٌ اَمع قَاعِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Is Zeyd standing, or sitting?"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqaAma zayodN A^amo","text_ar":"اَقَامَ زَيْدٌ اَمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEada","text_ar":"قَعَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Did Zeyd stand, or sit?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) It is not to be coupled with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a","text_ar":"اَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"after it: you may not say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEinodaka zayodN A^amo A^aEinodaka EamorNw","text_ar":"اَعِنْدَكَ زَيْدٌ اَمْ اَعِنْدَكَ عَمْرٌو"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-  As connected in like manner with what goes before, it is preceded by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a","text_ar":"اَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"denoting equality [by occurring after"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaA='N","text_ar":"سَوَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.], and corresponds thereto, as in [the Kur lxiii. 6,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaA='u Ealayohimo A^asotagofarota lahumN lamN tasotagufiro lahumN","text_ar":"سَوَا=ءُ عَلَيْهِمْ اَسْتَغْفَرْتَ لَهُمٌ لَمٌ تَسْتَغُفِرْ لَهُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[It will be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"equal to them whether thou beg forgiveness for them or do not beg forgiveness for them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mughnee.) ―         -b3-  It is also unconnected with what precedes it, (S, Msb, Mughnee,) implying always digression, (Mughnee,) preceded by an enunciative, or an interrogative, (S, Msb, Mughnee,) other than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a","text_ar":"اَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mughnee,) or by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a","text_ar":"اَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"not meant [really] as an interrogative but to denote disapproval, (Mughnee,) and signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balo","text_ar":"بَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, Zj, T, S, M, Mughnee, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balo","text_ar":"بَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a","text_ar":"اَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"together, (Msb,) and this is its meaning always accord. to all the Basrees, but the Koofees deny this. (Mughnee.) Thus, using it after an enunciative, you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahaA laA_ibilN A^amo $aA='N","text_ar":"اـِنَّهَا لَاـِبِلٌ اَمْ شَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily they are camels: nay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nay but, they are sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nay, are they sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S Msb, Mughnee:) this being said when one looks at a bodily form, and imagines it to be a number of camels, and says what first occurs to him; then the opinion that it is a number of sheep or goats suggests itself to him, and he turns from the first idea, and says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amo $aA='N","text_ar":"اَمْ شَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balo","text_ar":"بَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because it is a digression from what precedes it; though what follows"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bl","text_ar":"بل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [properly] a thing known certainly, and what follows"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Am","text_ar":"ام"},{"kind":"text","text":"is opined. (S, TA.) And using it after an interrogative in this case, you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halo zyodN","text_ar":"هَلْ زيْدٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munoTaliqN A^amo EamorNw","text_ar":"مُنْطَلِقٌ اَمْ عَمْرٌو"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Is Zeyd going away? Nay rather,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or rather, is 'Amr?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: you digress from the question respecting Zeyd's going away, and make the question to relate to 'Amr; so that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Am","text_ar":"ام"},{"kind":"text","text":"implies indecisive opinion, and interrogation, and digression. (S.) And thus using it, you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halo zayodN","text_ar":"هَلْ زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAma A^amo EamorNw","text_ar":"قَامَ اَمْ عَمْرٌو"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Did Zeyd stand? Nay rather,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or rather, did 'Amr?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) And an ex. of the same is the saying [in the Kur xiii. 17],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halo yasotawiY AloA^aEomaY waAlobaSiyru A^amo halo tasotawiY AlZ~ulumaAtu","text_ar":"هَلْ يَسْتَوِى الْاَعْمَى وَالْبَصِيرُ اَمْ هَلْ تَسْتَوِى الظُّلُمَاتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAln~uwru","text_ar":"وَالنُّورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Are the blind and the seeing equal? Or rather are darkness and light equal?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mughnee.) And an ex. of it preceded by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a","text_ar":"اَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"used to denote disapproval is the saying [in the Kur vii. 194],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alahumo A^arojulN yamo$uwna bihaA A^amo lahumo A^ayodK yaboTi$uwna bihaA","text_ar":"اَلَهُمْ اَرْجُلٌ يَمْشُونَ بِهَا اَمْ لَهُمْ اَيْدٍ يَبْطِشُونَ بِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Have they feet, to walk therewith? Or have they hands to assault therewith?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a","text_ar":"اَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here equivalent to a negation. (Mughnee.) [It has been shown above that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amo","text_ar":"اَمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes introduced immediately before"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halo","text_ar":"هَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) but IB says that this is when"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hl","text_ar":"هل"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in a phrase next before it; [as in the ex. from the Kur xiii. 17, cited above;] and in this case, the interrogative meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Am","text_ar":"ام"},{"kind":"text","text":"is annulled; it being introduced only to denote a digression. (TA.) ―         -b4-  It is also used as a simple interrogative; accord. to the assertion of AO; in"},{"kind":"page_break","n":89},{"kind":"text","text":"the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halo","text_ar":"هَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mughnee;) or in the sense of the interrogative"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a","text_ar":"اَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lth, T, K) as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amo Einodaka gadaA='i HaADirN","text_ar":"اَمْ عِنْدَكَ غَدَا=ءِ حَاضِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hast thou a morning-meal ready?"},{"kind":"text","text":"a good form of speech used by the Arabs; (Lth, T;) and allowable when preceded by another phrase. (T.) ―         -b5-  And sometimes it is redundant; (AZ, T, S, Mughnee, K) in the dial. of the people of El-Yemen; (T;) as in the saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yaA dahona A^amo maA kaAna ma$oyiY rqaSaA\n                      \n                     \n                        balo qado takuwnu mi$oyatiY tawaq~uSaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, * [in the latter,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yA hinodu","text_ar":"يا هِنْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and only the former hemistich is given,]) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O Dahnà,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the curtailed form"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahona","text_ar":"دَهْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahonaA='","text_ar":"دَهْنَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my walking was not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as now in my age, [a feeble movement like]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dancing: but"},{"kind":"text","text":"in my youth,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my manner of walking used to be a bounding:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) this is accord. to the opinion of AZ: but accord. to another opinion,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Am","text_ar":"ام"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here [virtually] conjoined with a preceding clause which is suppressed; as though the speaker had said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA dahona A^akaAna ma$oyiY","text_ar":"يَا دَهْنَ اَكَانَ مَشْيِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqaS~aA A^amo maA kaAna ka*lika","text_ar":"رَقَصَّا اَمْ مَا كَانَ كَذلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A 'Hát, TA.)       -A2-  It is also used (T, Mughnee) in the dial. of the people of El-Yemen, (T,) or of Teiyi and Himyer, (Mughnee,) in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,) to render a noun determinate. (Mughnee.) So in the trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa mina Amobir~ AmoSiyAmu fiY Amosafari","text_ar":"لَيْسَ مِنَ امْبِرّ امْصِيامُ فِى امْسَفَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, Mughnee,) i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alayosa mina Albir~i AlS~iyaAmu fiY Als~afari","text_ar":"الَيْسَ مِنَ البِرِّ الصِّيَامُ فِى السَّفَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fasting in journeying is not"},{"kind":"text","text":"an act"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of obedience"},{"kind":"text","text":"to God]. (T, and M in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"br","text_ar":"بر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) So too in the trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AaloA=na","text_ar":"اَلْا=نَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAba AmoDarobu","text_ar":"طَابَ امْضَرْبُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Now fighting has become lawful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as related accord. to the dial. of Himyer, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~arobu","text_ar":"الضَّرْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tyb","text_ar":"طيب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) It has been said that this form"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Am","text_ar":"ام"},{"kind":"text","text":"is only used in those cases in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the article does not become incorporated into the first letter of the noun to which it is prefixed; as in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*i Alr~umoHa waArokabi Amofarasa","text_ar":"خُذِ الرُّمْحَ وَارْكَبِ امْفَرَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou the spear, and mount the mare,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"], related as heard in El-Yemen; but this usage may be peculiar to some of the people of that country; not common to all of them; as appears from what we have cited above. (Mughnee.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ama","text_ar":"اَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaA","text_ar":"اَمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", before an oath: see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AmA","text_ar":"اما"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ama All~`hi","text_ar":"اَمَ اللّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amu All~`hi","text_ar":"اَمُ اللّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayomunu All~`hi","text_ar":"اَيْمُنُ اللّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ymn","text_ar":"يمن"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","Msb","Lth","T"]},{"entry_id":"n1170","headword_ar":"اُمٌّ","root":"Am","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mother"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Msb, K, &c.) [of a human being and] of any animal; (IAar, T;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_im~N","text_ar":"اـِمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, M, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_um~apN","text_ar":"اـُمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~ahapN","text_ar":"اُمَّهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) which last is the original form (S, Msb) accord. to some, (Msb,) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this is augmentative (M, Msb) accord. to others: (Msb:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~ahaAtN","text_ar":"اُمَّهَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~aAtN","text_ar":"اُمَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, Msb, K;) or the former is applied to human beings, and the latter to beasts; (T, S;) or the former to rational beings, and the latter to irrational; (M, K;) or the former is much applied to human beings, and the latter to others, for the sake of distinction; (Msb;) but the reverse is sometimes the case: (IB:) IDrst and others hold the latter to be of weak authority: (TA:) the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~N","text_ar":"اُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^umayomapN","text_ar":"اُمَيْمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K) accord. to some of the Arabs; but correctly, [accord. to those who hold the original form of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~N","text_ar":"اُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~ahapN","text_ar":"اُمَّهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] it is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^umayomihapN","text_ar":"اُمَيْمِهَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lth, T, TA. [In a copy of the T, I find this latter form of the dim. written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Amyhp","text_ar":"اميهة"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~a laka","text_ar":"اُمَّ لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"denotes dispraise; (S;) being used by the Arabs as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast no"},{"kind":"text","text":"free, or ingenuous,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mother;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the sons of female slaves are objects of dispraise with the Arabs; and is only said in anger and reviling: (A Heyth, T:) or, as some say, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thou art one"},{"kind":"text","text":"who has been picked up as a foundling,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no"},{"kind":"text","text":"Known"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mother:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [or] it is also sometimes used in praise; (A 'Obeyd, T, S, K;) and is used as an imprecation without the desire of its being fulfilled upon the person addressed, being said in vehemence of love; [lit. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mayest thou have no mother!"},{"kind":"text","text":"], like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vakilatoka A^um~uka","text_ar":"ثَكِلَتْكَ اُمُّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^abaA laka","text_ar":"لَا اَبَا لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAtalaka All~`hu","text_ar":"قَاتَلَكَ اللّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] &c. (Har p. 165.) ―         -b3-  Some elide the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~","text_ar":"اُمّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as in the saying of 'Adee Ibn—Zeyd."},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^ay~uhaA AlEaAy^ibu Einodim~a zayodK"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O thou who art blaming in my presence the mother of Zeyd"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinodiY A^um~a zayodK","text_ar":"عِنْدِى اُمَّ زَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EndY","text_ar":"عندى"},{"kind":"text","text":"being also elided on account of the occurrence of two quiescent letters [after the elision of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~","text_ar":"اُمّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Lth, T, S:) and as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayolum~ihi","text_ar":"وَيْلُمِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) which means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayolN liA^um~ihi","text_ar":"وَيْلٌ لِاُمِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wyl","text_ar":"ويل"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaA A^um~aAk~","text_ar":"هُمَا اُمَّاكّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They two are thy two parents:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy mother and thy maternal aunt."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [But]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fad~aAhu biA^um~ayohi","text_ar":"فَدَّاهُ بِاُمَّيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to mean ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He expressed a wish that he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(another)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"might be ransomed with"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his mother and his grandmother."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tafoEaliY","text_ar":"لَا تَفْعَلِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA A^um~ati","text_ar":"يَا اُمَّتِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O my mother, do not thou"},{"kind":"text","text":"such a thing], and [in like manner]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA A^abati AfoEalo","text_ar":"يَا اَبَتِ افْعَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; making the sign of the fem. gender a substitute for the [pronominal] affix"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in a case of pause, you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA A^um~aho","text_ar":"يَا اُمَّهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b6-  And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^um~iY waA^um~uhu","text_ar":"مَا اُمِّى وَاُمُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA $akoliY wa$akoluhu","text_ar":"مَا شَكْلِى وَشَكْلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What relationship have I to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it?"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what concern have I with him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it?"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is my case and"},{"kind":"text","text":"[what is]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its, case?"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of his, or its, remoteness from me: whence, (T,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wamaA A^um~iY waA^um~u AlwaHo$i lam~aA\n                      \n                     \n                        tafar~aEa fiY mafaAriqiYa Aloma$iybu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And what concern have I with the wild animals when hoariness hath spread in the places where my hair parts?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (T, S;) i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^anaAwaTalabu","text_ar":"مَا اَنَاوَطَلَبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwaHo$i baEoda maA kabirotu","text_ar":"الوَحْشِ بَعْدَ مَا كَبِرْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^moriy waTalabu AlwaHo$i","text_ar":"مَا امْرِي وَطَلَبُ الوَحْشِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": in one copy of the S,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waTalaba","text_ar":"وَطَلَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa","text_ar":"وَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a prep. denoting concomitance, and therefore governing the accus. case: both readings virtually meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what concern have I with the pursuing of the wild animals after I have grown old?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: he means, the girls: and the mention of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~","text_ar":"اُمّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the verse is superfluous. (S.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~N","text_ar":"اُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also relates to inanimate things that have growth; as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Al$~ajarapi","text_ar":"اُمُّ الشَّجَرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The mother of the tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Aln~axolapi","text_ar":"اُمُّ النَّخْلَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the mother of the palm-tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Almawozipa","text_ar":"اُمُّ المَوْزِةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the mother of the banana-tree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"of which see an ex. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mwz","text_ar":"موز"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and the like. (M, TA.) ―         -b8-  And it signifies also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"source, origin, foundation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"basis,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K,) of a thing, (S, Msb, [in the former of which, this is the first of the meanings assigned to the word,]) or of anything; (M, K) its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stay, support,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"efficient cause of subsistence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything to which other things are collected together,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adjoined:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, M, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything to which the other things that are next thereto are collected together,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adjoined:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"main,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief, part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"main body"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof: and that which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a compriser,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comprehender,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of [other] things: (Ham p. 44:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of collection, comprisal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comprehension,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of combination"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (En-Nadr, T.) ―         -b10-  And hence, (IDrd, M,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people, or company of men; (IDrd, S, M, K;) because others collect themselves together to him: (IDrd, TA:) so in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u EiyaAlK","text_ar":"اُمُّ عِيَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the mother of a household"},{"kind":"text","text":"], in a poem of Esh-Shenfarà: (IDrd, M:) or in this instance, it has the signification next following, accord. to Esh-Sháfi'ee. (T.) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who has the charge of the food and service"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people, or company of men; accord. to EshSháfi'ee: (T:) or their"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"servant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b12-  A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aged wife."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, K.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of habitation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) So in the Kur [ci. 6],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^um~uhu haAwiyapN","text_ar":"فَاُمُّهُ هَاوِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His place of habitation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode"},{"kind":"text","text":"[shall be]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of Hell]: (Bd, Jel, TA:) or, as some say, the meaning is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u raA^osihi haAwiyapN fiyhaA","text_ar":"اُمُّ رَاْسِهِ هَاوِيَةٌ فِيهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his brain shall fall into it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, the fire of Hell]. (TA.) ―         -b14-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ensign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"standard, which an army follows."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Alr~umoHi","text_ar":"اُمُّ الرُّمْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.] ―         -b15-  It is said in a trad., respecting the prophets,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~ahaA tuhumo $at~aY","text_ar":"اُمَّهَا تُهُمْ شَتَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning that, though their religion is one,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their laws,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ordinances,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"statutes, are various,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"different:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their times are various,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"different."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$t","text_ar":"شت"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b16-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~apN","text_ar":"اُمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b17-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~","text_ar":"اُمّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also prefixed to nouns significant of many things. (M.) [Most of the compounds thus formed will be found explained in the arts. to which belong the nouns that occupy the second place. The following are among the more common, and are therefore here mentioned, with the meanings assigned to them in lexicons in the present art., and arranged in distinct classes.] ―         -b18-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Alr~ajuli","text_ar":"اُمُّ الرَّجُلِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man's wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the person who manages the affairs of his house"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u mavowaY Alr~ajuli","text_ar":"اُمُّ مَثْوَى الرَّجُلِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man's wife, to whom he betakes himself for lodging,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the mistress of the man's place of abode."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M.) ―         -b19-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u EaAmirK","text_ar":"اُمُّ عَامِرٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hyena,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female hyena;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u EamorKw","text_ar":"اُمُّ عَمْرٍو"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u AlT~ariyqi","text_ar":"اُمُّ الطَّرِيقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA. [See also other significations of the first and last below.])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u HilosK","text_ar":"اُمُّ حِلْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u AlHilosi","text_ar":"اُمُّ الحِلْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(as in the S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hlas","text_ar":"حلَس"},{"kind":"text","text":")]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The she-ass."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u AlbayoDi","text_ar":"اُمُّ البَيْضِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The female ostrich."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b20-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Alr~aA^usi","text_ar":"اُمُّ الرَّاُسِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The brain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thin skin that is upon it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the bag in which is the brain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the skin that comprises the brain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the meninx,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dura mater and pia mater;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, Mgh;) which is called"},{"kind":"page_break","n":90},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Ald~imaAgi","text_ar":"اُمُّ الدِّمَاغِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) likewise. (S.) ―         -b21-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Aln~ujuwmi","text_ar":"اُمُّ النُّجُومِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Milky way;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) because it is the place where the stars are collected together [in great multitude]: (M:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sun;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is the greatest of the stars. (Ham pp. 43 and 44.) Because of the multitude of the stars in the Milky way, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^a$obaha majolisaka biA^um~i","text_ar":"مَا اَشْبَهَ مَجْلِسَكَ بِاُمِّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~ujuwmi","text_ar":"النُّجُومِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How like is thine assembly to the Milky way!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b22-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u AlquraY","text_ar":"اُمُّ القُرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The mother of the towns; the metropolis:"},{"kind":"text","text":"particularly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mekkeh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K) because asserted to be in the middle of the earth; (M, K;) or because it is the Kibleh of all men, and thither they repair; (M, K; *) or because it is the greatest of towns in dignity: (M, K:) and every city is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~","text_ar":"اُمّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the towns around it. (T.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Alt~anaAy^ifi","text_ar":"اُمُّ التَّنَايِفِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The most difficult of deserts"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of waterless deserts:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a desert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waterless desert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"far extending."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u AlT~ariyqi","text_ar":"اُمُّ الطَّرِيقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~apN","text_ar":"اُمَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~ariyqi","text_ar":"الطَّرِيقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The main part"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"track"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the road:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it is a great road"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"track, with small roads"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tracks around it"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on either side"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the greatest is so called."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T. [The former has also another signification, mentioned above.])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u EaAmirK","text_ar":"اُمُّ عَامِرٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cemetery,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of graves."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T. [This, also, has another signification, mentioned before.])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Alr~umoHi","text_ar":"اُمُّ الرُّمْحِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ensign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"standard;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u AlHarobi","text_ar":"اُمُّ الحَرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) [and simply"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^um~u","text_ar":"الاُمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as shown above;] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the piece of cloth which is wound upon the spear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M. *)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u jaAbirK","text_ar":"اُمُّ جَابِرٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bread:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the ear of corn."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u AlxabaAy^ivi","text_ar":"اُمُّ الخَبَايِثِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The mother of evil qualities"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispositions;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wine."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u","text_ar":"اُمُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkitaAbi","text_ar":"الكِتَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the Kur iii. 5 and xiii. 39] (S, M, &c.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The original of the book"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scripture"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Kur-án"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Zj, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Preserved Tablet,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~awoHu AlmaHofuwZu","text_ar":"اللَّوْحُ المَحْفُوظُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, Msb, K:) or it signifies, (M, K,) or signifies also, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the opening chapter of the Kur-án; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAtiHap","text_ar":"فَاتِحَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Msb, K;) because every prayer begins therewith; (M;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u AlquroA=ni","text_ar":"اُمُّ القُرْا=نِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, K:) or the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the whole of the Kur-án,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(I'Ab, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from its beginning to its end:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"explicit, verse of the Kur-án, of those which relate to laws and statutes and obligatory ordinances."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Al$~ar~i","text_ar":"اُمُّ الشَّرِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Every evil upon the face of the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Alxayori","text_ar":"اُمُّ الخَيْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every good upon the face of the earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.)"}],"source_refs":["Sb","M","Msb","K","T","S","Lth","IB","TA","IDrd","Bd","Jel","Zj"]},{"entry_id":"n1171","headword_ar":"اـِمُّ","root":"Am","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~N","text_ar":"اُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}